This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and information retrieval applications. The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for dynamic entity relatedness, which is a common task in NLP and IR. Additionally, the paper leverages collective attention as supervision, which is a popular technique in CL. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it deals with entity relatedness ranking, which is a common task in IR. 

The sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely because the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for learning entity representations. 

The sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible because the paper deals with a fundamental task in AI, i.e., measuring entity relatedness. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also possible because the paper deals with dynamic entity relations, which are often modeled as networks in SI.
